-- ArcelorMittal, BHP, Kumba, SacOil: South African Equity Preview
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s   a n d   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 2010-10-05T05:46:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/altron-arcelormittal-gold-reef-may-move-south-african-equities-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in South Africa.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  gained
28.24, or 0.1 percent, to 29,294.97 in Johannesburg.  Allied Electronics Corp. Ltd.  (ATN SJ), an investment group
with interests in communications equipment, said first-half
profit climbed 21 percent to 294 million rand ($42 million). The
stock fell 32 cents, or 1.2 percent, to 26.67 rand.  ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd.  (ACL SJ), Africa’s largest
steelmaker, won’t win the support of South Africa’s Public
Investment Corp. for a deal with black investors until a
“number of concerns” and “perceived irregularities” are
resolved, the state’s pension funds manager said. The steel
company gained 64 cents, or 0.8 percent, to 83 rand.  BHP Billiton Ltd.  (BIL SJ), the world’s biggest mining
company, has more time to win its bid to buy  Potash Corp. of
Saskatchewan Inc.  after Canada extended the deadline to review
BHP’s $40 billion hostile takeover offer by an additional 30
days. BHP dropped 29 cents, or 0.1 percent, to 225.61 rand.  Gold Reef Resorts Ltd.  (GDF SJ) plans to make
representations to South Africa’s Competition Tribunal to obtain
unconditional approval for its planned merger with Tsogo Sun
Holdings Ltd. The Competition Commission recommended that the
tribunal should make the disposal of Silverstar Casino
conditional to the merger, Gold Reef said. Gold Reef rose 75
cents, or 4.3 percent, to 18.10 rand.  Kumba Iron Ore Ltd.  (KIO SJ), a unit of  Anglo American Plc ,
reached a pay agreement with South Africa’s National Union of
Mineworkers in an effort to end a strike that started yesterday.
Kumba retreated 6.63 rand, or 1.8 percent, to 362.32 rand.  Northam Platinum Ltd.  (NHM SJ) made a new pay offer to
workers on strike at the company’s only mine, Zondereinde, for
the 30th day, a National Union of Mineworkers spokesman said.
The offer will be presented to members of the union tomorrow,
Ecliff Tantsi said by mobile phone today. Northam increased 26
cents, or 0.6 percent, to 47.80 rand.  SacOil Holdings Ltd.  (SCL SJ), an oil company with
concessions in Democratic Republic of Congo, scheduled a press
conference on its future plans. SacOil lost 7 cents, or 7.4
percent, to 88 cents.  Zeder Investments Ltd.  (ZED SJ), a group with holdings in
agriculture companies, said profit rose 22 percent to 96.5
million rand in the six months through Aug. 31 from a year
earlier. Zeder was unchanged at 2.20 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 1.2 percent to $20.04.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) slid 2 percent to $46.14. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) lost 1.7 percent to $64.18. DRDGold Ltd.
(DROOY US) dropped 0.4 percent to $5.23. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) declined 0.3 percent to $15.22. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY
US) retreated 0.7 percent to $11.24. Impala Platinum Holdings
Co. (IMPUY US) gained 1.7 percent to $26.45. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
fell 0.4 percent to $5.16. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) was almost
unchanged at $45.21.  To contact the reporters on this story:
